In England, in the seven days to 09 October, there were 212,697 new confirmed cases (376.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 October, there were 188,509 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 13% (24,188 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 October is 7,073,467 (12,508.3 cases per 100,000 population).
